The Sri Lanka Export Development Board, usually known as EDB, is Sri Lanka's apex organization for the promotion and development of exports and was established in 1979 under the Sri Lanka Export Development Act No. 40.

EDB is the executive arm of the Export Development Council of Ministers, which is the policy-making body of the EDB. It is headed by H.E. the President of Sri Lanka.

The goal of EDB is to provide assistance and create opportunities for Sri Lankan companies to expand their business internationally, thereby increasing export sales and employment prospects in the region. EDBs staff offers consultative services to small- and mid-sized businesses located throughout Sri Lanka. EDBs also sponsors and co-sponsors educational seminars and training programs designed for exporters and potential exporters in the region.

description:
A luxury bed & Breakfast located in five acres of the Sri Lankan Hill Country near Beragala, Haputale. 

Three king-size bedrooms with en suites and superb views of the valley below leading to the Southern Hills. 

A Natural Spring Fed Infinity Swimming Pool is surrounded by nature and a great place to relax.

Food is prepared freshly by Ruwanthi and the team.

Vegetarian and vegan options are available, plus some fish and chicken dishes to order.

We source a majority of the food from our organic garden or from local producers.

If you want to get away from the stresses and hustle and bustle of everyday life, GlenMyu Estate is a great place to holiday. 

We only have three bedrooms and therefore you will need to book early.

Please visit our website http://resortglenmyu.com for more information, rates, and offers. 

We are on Airbnb and Booking.com - have a look at our customer reviews. 

Find us also on Instagram.

description:
Kalutara , A charming beach town of Sri Lankan west coast has a lot to offer for an ardent traveller. Set foot in golden sands fringed with palm trees and behold the mighty Kalu river meets Indian Ocean concluding her journey starting form lush green hills. 

You should travel Kalutara to experience not only for its golden beaches and but also for culture and authenticity. Where you'll find one of the most venerated Bodhi tree (Kalutara Bodhiya) along with the world's only hollow pagoda (Kalutara Chaitya) which is a pioneering engineering project of Sri Lanka and adorns the view when you pass the Kalutara bridge and enter the city.

For adventures travellers there are many things to do in Kalutara. Hop in a kayak , boat or Oruwa (Traditional Sri Lankan boat type) and conquer the calm waters of Kalu river.
